53. Maximum Subarray
Problem

Given an integer array:

nums[]

Find the contiguous subarray with the largest sum and return that sum.

Example
Input
nums = [-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4]
Output
6
Maximum Subarray
[4,-1,2,1]

Sum:

6
Brute Force Approach
Intuition

Generate all possible subarrays.

Calculate sum of each subarray.

Return maximum sum.

Algorithm
1. Start from every index
2. Extend subarray one by one
3. Keep calculating sum
4. Update maximum sum
Brute Force Code
class Solution {
    public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {

        int maxSum = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for(int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {

            int sum = 0;

            for(int j = i; j < nums.length; j++) {

                sum += nums[j];

                maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, sum);
            }
        }

        return maxSum;
    }
}
Complexity
Time Complexity
O(n²)
Space Complexity
O(1)
Optimal Approach — Kadane’s Algorithm

Most important interview solution.

Main Intuition

If current sum becomes negative:

it will decrease future sums

So discard it and start a new subarray.

Core Idea

Maintain:

currentSum → current subarray sum
maxSum     → maximum sum found so far
Rules
Add current element
currentSum += nums[i]
Update maximum
maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, currentSum)
If currentSum becomes negative
currentSum = 0

Because negative sum cannot help future subarrays.

Important Intuition

Suppose:

currentSum = -5

Next element:

10

Continuing gives:

-5 + 10 = 5

Starting fresh gives:

10

So negative prefix should be removed.

