Optimal Java Code
class Solution {
    public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {

        int currentSum = 0;
        int maxSum = nums[0];

        for(int num : nums) {

            currentSum += num;

            maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, currentSum);

            if(currentSum < 0) {
                currentSum = 0;
            }
        }

        return maxSum;
    }
}
Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
O(n)

Only one traversal.

Space Complexity
O(1)

No extra space used.

Important Interview Points
Why reset currentSum when it becomes negative?

Because a negative prefix can never help in getting a larger future sum.

Why initialize maxSum = nums[0]?

To correctly handle cases where all elements are negative.

Example:

nums = [-1]

Answer should be:

-1

not 0.

